                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/1331: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-18T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 18, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>689. From the Under Secretary. Your 954, July 28, 6 p.m. Please telegraph me at
                    the earliest possible moment whether the question which President Vargas said he
                    was submitting to the consideration of the Mixed Commission of General Staff
                    officers has yet been decided. The War Department here has no information on
                    this point and neither have I. I shall appreciate it if you can send me this
                    information rapidly, particularly if the reply is favorable, [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
